known you for 40 years,

10:06.406 --> 10:08.607
but I think washing
your underwear for even one day

10:08.609 --> 10:10.308
puts me in the inner sanctum.

10:10.310 --> 10:13.044
I...I could be
your best friend.

10:13.046 --> 10:14.145
What?

10:14.147 --> 10:16.047
I'll be your new Gigi!

10:16.049 --> 10:17.415
Bow, don't be ridiculous.

10:17.417 --> 10:19.551
You're my wife, not my friend.

10:19.553 --> 10:22.587
Well, come on. I love shopping.
I love manicures.

10:22.589 --> 10:25.056
Put me in, coach.
[ Chuckles ] I got this.

10:25.058 --> 10:27.225
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

10:27.227 --> 10:28.827
We'll try this out.
Okay.

10:28.829 --> 10:31.830
But don't you dare say
you love manicures

10:31.832 --> 10:35.066
because those gels
are six weeks old.

10:35.068 --> 10:37.669
Already starting
on the wrong foot, friend.

10:37.671 --> 10:39.104
Dre.
Let's get it together.

10:39.106 --> 10:40.939
My nails are poppin'.

10:40.941 --> 10:42.774
No, they're not.

10:42.776 --> 10:46.144
♪ I keep on fallin' ♪

10:46.146 --> 10:48.279
♪ In and out ♪

10:48.281 --> 10:49.914
♪ Of love ♪

10:49.916 --> 10:51.282
♪ With you ♪

10:51.284 --> 10:55.353
♪ I never loved someone ♪

10:55.355 --> 10:59.324
♪ The way that I love you ♪

10:59.326 --> 11:01.860
Wow!
That was awesome!

11:01.862 --> 11:03.161
We got to shoot this now.

11:03.163 --> 11:04.496
[ Chuckles ]
Absolutely.

11:04.498 --> 11:07.465
I just have one quick question.

11:07.467 --> 11:10.435
Jack, did you mean to clap
on the one and the three?

11:10.437 --> 11:11.670
Yes.

11:11.672 --> 11:13.672
Do you even know
what the one and the three are?

11:16.043 --> 11:17.142
Yes?

11:17.144 --> 11:18.843
Well, show me.
Right now.

11:18.845 --> 11:20.345
[ Chuckles ]

11:21.982 --> 11:24.349
I'm sorry.
Is this a joke to you?

11:24.351 --> 11:27.352
Take it easy, Diane.
We're just having a little fun.

11:27.354 --> 11:29.187
Oh. Mm-Kay.

11:29.189 --> 11:33.058
So, it's fun
to miss a key change?

11:33.060 --> 11:35.894
It's fun
to be off-tempo?

11:35.896 --> 11:37.729
Because if it is [Chuckles]

11:37.731 --> 11:40.398
You guys are having
the time of your life.

11:40.400 --> 11:43.234
Uh, maybe we should all
just take five.

11:43.236 --> 11:45.103
Not till you tell me
what's fun about this?

11:46.373 --> 11:48.306
What is fun about this?!

11:49.710 --> 11:52.911
<i>So, bow and I took our new
best-friend relationship</i>

11:52.913 --> 11:54.412
<i>out for a spin.</i>

11:54.414 --> 11:57.148
<i>Honestly,
it started a little bumpy.</i>

11:57.150 --> 12:00.218
Aha! What do you
think, hmm?

12:00.220 --> 12:02.520
That's great.
I love it.

12:02.522 --> 12:04.989
Mindless compliment, huh?

12:04.991 --> 12:07.092
Okay, look, this was a mistake.

12:07.094 --> 12:10.328
What? Let's just go home, and
I will die best-friendless.

12:10.330 --> 12:13.998
"Here lies Andre Johnson,
survived by acquaintances."

12:14.000 --> 12:15.266
Wh... Dre, no, no.

12:15.268 --> 12:16.768
Let me... let me try again.
Come on.

12:16.770 --> 12:18.036
Okay.
All right.

12:18.038 --> 12:20.405
Now, is this
too matchy-matchy,

12:20.407 --> 12:23.208
or is this good denim-on-denim?
Talk to me.

12:23.210 --> 12:25.076
I genuinely like it.
Oh.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.678
I feel like it's just off enough
that it's perfect.

12:26.680 --> 12:27.579
Okay, cool.

12:27.581 --> 12:30.582
How about if I...
Oh, god.

12:30.584 --> 12:32.283
Add this jacket, huh?

12:32.285 --> 12:34.085
Okay, okay.

12:34.087 --> 12:36.921
Just... just, like...
Just getting<i> all</i> the denim.

12:36.923 --> 12:38.089
Come on, bow, I'm gonna need

12:38.091 --> 12:40.091
gigi-level honesty here,
all right?

12:40.093 --> 12:42.093
Okay.
Okay, you...

12:42.095 --> 12:43.795
You look like a farmer

12:43.797 --> 12:47.632
attending his daughter's wedding
in Alberta.

12:47.634 --> 12:48.967
Ah! That was good!
Yeah?

12:48.969 --> 12:50.235
That was a good one.
Okay!

12:50.237 --> 12:51.469
Yeah!

12:51.471 --> 12:52.771
Okay, wait, I-i-i have another one.
Really?

12:52.773 --> 12:54.305
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Okay, hit me with it.

12:54.307 --> 12:56.407
Uh, those skinny jeans
make your legs look like

12:56.409 --> 12:57.942
you've been in a wheelchair

12:57.944 --> 13:00.044
for the last 20 years
of your life.

13:00.046 --> 13:01.446
[ Laughs ]

13:01.448 --> 13:02.981
[ Chuckles ]

13:02.983 --> 13:05.450
Sounds like that one's been locked
and loaded for a minute now.

13:05.452 --> 13:06.918
[ Laughing ]
'Cause your legs are small.

13:06.920 --> 13:08.386
Yeah, yeah,
my legs are small. Okay.

13:08.388 --> 13:10.155
Um, well, the goal is

13:10.157 --> 13:13.158
to, uh, be honest
and, uh, not cruel.

13:13.160 --> 13:15.160
We'll find it.
We'll find it.

13:15.162 --> 13:16.728
Yeah, but, you know,
we're off to a good start.

13:16.730 --> 13:17.962
Oh. Wow.

13:17.964 --> 13:20.231
You know what?
That jumpsuit is dope.

13:20.233 --> 13:21.166
You like it?
I don't know.

13:21.168 --> 13:22.300
Yeah, it makes your butt

13:22.302 --> 13:24.068
look like that peach tower
on "house of cards."

13:24.070 --> 13:25.136
I'm gonna buy this.
Okay. High five!

13:25.138 --> 13:26.404
Okay. High five.
We did good.

13:26.406 --> 13:27.338
[ Both laughing ]

13:27.340 --> 13:29.107
This is so much fun, friend!

13:29.109 --> 13:31.776
Trust me, Di,
I know you're frustrated.

13:31.778 --> 13:34.279
It's hard when you're
as talented as you and I are.

13:34.281 --> 13:35.814
But it's not just about talent.

13:35.816 --> 13:37.182
It can be lonely at the top.

13:37.184 --> 13:40.185
All these private jets
and five-star hotels

13:40.187 --> 13:42.353
and endangered-species
dinners and...

13:42.355 --> 13:44.255
Wait, endangered species?

13:44.257 --> 13:47.258
Are you raising money
to help them or...

13:47.260 --> 13:48.927
I ate the last dodo.

13:48.929 --> 13:50.795
I want to eat
the last something.

13:50.797 --> 13:53.665
Of course you do.
Everybody does.

13:53.667 --> 13:55.133
But you don't want
to eat it alone.

13:55.135 --> 13:57.101
Di, success means nothing

13:57.103 --> 13:59.337
if you don't have somebody
to share the ride with.

14:00.340 --> 14:01.973
Thanks.

14:01.975 --> 14:03.975
I know what I have to do.

14:03.977 --> 14:06.678
I'm going solo, guys.
Best of luck.

14:06.680 --> 14:08.680
[ Chuckles ]
You're probably going to fail.

14:11.284 --> 14:13.451
She doesn't mean that, right?

14:15.856 --> 14:17.222
Right?

14:17.224 --> 14:19.324
Annie, don't be afraid
to hit them heels, all right?

14:19.326 --> 14:20.658
Make her feet soft like mine.

14:20.660 --> 14:23.027
You do have pillowy feet, Dre.

14:23.029 --> 14:24.729
You can, too, baby.

14:24.731 --> 14:26.698
Only five short hours
to perfect feet.

14:26.700 --> 14:28.466
Whoa, five hours?
Mm-hmm.

14:28.468 --> 14:31.202
It takes less time
to remove a brain tumor.

14:31.204 --> 14:34.339
But can a brain tumor
wear an open-toe sandal? No.

14:34.341 --> 14:35.640
No.

14:35.642 --> 14:37.675
All right, this isn't
just a pedicure, okay?

14:37.677 --> 14:39.577
It's a paraffin dip,
it's a sea-salt scrub,

14:39.579 --> 14:40.745
it's a Brazilian wax, then
they gonna sugar-wax your...

14:40.747 --> 14:42.981
Stop. Stop, stop, stop,
stop, stop.

14:42.983 --> 14:44.916
Dre, you get
a bro-zilian?

14:44.918 --> 14:46.818
Well, those are
the things that you learn

14:46.820 --> 14:48.186
with your best friend.

14:48.188 --> 14:50.188
Like I learned
that you have the feet

14:50.190 --> 14:52.090
of a Kenyan distance runner.

14:52.092 --> 14:53.091
[ Chuckles ]
Ellen.

14:53.093 --> 14:54.726
[ Speaks Vietnamese ]

14:54.728 --> 14:55.927
[ Both laugh ]

14:55.929 --> 14:57.695
Do you speak...
Viet..Namese?

14:57.697 --> 14:59.230
[ Laughter ]
I didn't know that.

14:59.232 --> 15:00.765
Are you...
Are you talking about me?

15:00.767 --> 15:02.734
What? No.

15:02.736 --> 15:04.602
[ Speaking Vietnamese ]
Rainbow Johnson.

15:04.604 --> 15:07.105
[ Speaking Vietnamese ]

15:07.107 --> 15:09.874
The gods must be crazy.
[ Laughs ]

15:09.876 --> 15:11.242
What did you say?

15:11.244 --> 15:13.244
[ Speaking Vietnamese ]

15:13.246 --> 15:14.612
[ Laughter ]

15:14.614 --> 15:15.947
Why's everybody laughing?

15:15.949 --> 15:17.415
Oh, 'cause I told her
just take a little off the top.

15:17.417 --> 15:20.919
[ Laughter ]

15:25.258 --> 15:26.424
Rainbow:
Ugh. You were right.

15:26.426 --> 15:27.425
This best-friend thing was
a huge mistake.

15:27.427 --> 15:29.627
He's totally getting worse, Pam.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.195
He just texted me 10 seconds ago

15:31.197 --> 15:34.232
about a text he sent
20 seconds ago.

15:34.234 --> 15:36.434
Yeah, can you just call me
on my home phone, please,

15:36.436 --> 15:39.404
and, like, say there's, like,
I don't know, a massive fire

15:39.406 --> 15:41.105
or something,
and I'm needed at work?

15:41.107 --> 15:42.941
Just get me out of here!
Okay, bye.

15:42.943 --> 15:44.375
[ Cellphone chimes ]

15:44.377 --> 15:47.145
Oh, my god. Stop it.
Leave me Al...

15:47.147 --> 15:49.213
Dre: Bow!
[ Gasps ]

15:49.215 --> 15:51.916
Aah!! Oh!
Hey, my best friend!

15:51.918 --> 15:53.051
[ Chuckles ]

15:53.053 --> 15:54.585
Hey, hey, check this out.

15:54.587 --> 15:58.089
Gigi just posted,
"having fun with my boo."

15:58.091 --> 15:59.257
Oh.

15:59.259 --> 16:01.225
It's her and Napoleon
getting mani-pedis.

16:01.227 --> 16:02.994
Oh, no.
Look at her.

16:02.996 --> 16:05.163
You should go down there,
like, right now.

16:05.165 --> 16:08.399
Like, leave this minute.
Like, leave this house.

16:08.401 --> 16:11.602
Just get out of here. No,
<i>I'm</i> not going down there.

16:11.604 --> 16:14.272
Oh.
<i>We're</i> going down there.

16:14.274 --> 16:15.840
We're go...
Uh-huh.

16:15.842 --> 16:17.342
I'm gonna show them
what this magic is like.

16:17.344 --> 16:18.843
Okay.
Come on. Let's go.

16:18.845 --> 16:19.777
Okay.

16:19.779 --> 16:22.180
[ Vocalizing ]

16:23.616 --> 16:25.750
♪ 5-foot 2 with some attitude ♪

16:25.752 --> 16:28.486
♪ And I can tell that she get it
from mama ♪

16:28.488 --> 16:30.488
♪ Go ahead, get loose with it ♪

16:30.490 --> 16:31.756
♪ Girl, don't be stuck up ♪

16:31.758 --> 16:33.024
♪ Get up ♪

16:33.026 --> 16:35.426
♪ Put your hands in the air,
now, jump, jump ♪

16:35.428 --> 16:37.595
♪ Came in here
to have fun, fun ♪

16:37.597 --> 16:40.431
♪ Now, do your dance,
don't be shy ♪

16:40.433 --> 16:42.100
♪ Go to work
like a 9:00-to-5:00 ♪

16:42.102 --> 16:44.602
♪ In your mirror, on
your chair ♪ excuse me!

16:44.604 --> 16:45.503
[ Music stops ]

16:45.505 --> 16:47.472
Siblings...

16:47.474 --> 16:51.142
It's a lonely perch
for a solo artist,

16:51.144 --> 16:54.379
so I come to you hat in hand.

16:54.381 --> 16:55.780
I want back in.

16:55.782 --> 16:57.215
Yes!
Oh, thank god.

16:57.217 --> 16:59.650
Well, wait a second.
Why should we let her back in?

16:59.652 --> 17:02.353
Zoey, you're still
kind of finding your voice.

17:02.355 --> 17:03.788
You can't sing.

17:03.790 --> 17:06.157
Check out what
we've been working on.

17:06.159 --> 17:08.526
[<i> Slow-tempo music plays</i> ]

17:08.528 --> 17:10.862
Zoey: [ Off-key ]
<i>♪ don't let it pass you by ♪</i>

17:10.864 --> 17:12.964
<i>♪ black girl glitter
makes you high ♪</i>

17:12.966 --> 17:15.066
<i>♪ and if people ask you why ♪</i>

17:15.068 --> 17:17.068
<i>♪ tell 'em it's
because you're fly ♪</i>

17:17.070 --> 17:18.803
[ Music stops ]

17:21.074 --> 17:23.274
You know what, guys?
I'm good.

17:24.411 --> 17:27.712
Trust your gut, Diane.

17:27.714 --> 17:29.347
Thanks, Nikki.
Okay, so, here?

17:29.349 --> 17:30.648
Thank you, Nikki.

17:30.650 --> 17:31.416
Hello.

17:31.418 --> 17:32.750
Oh.
Hi.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.485
Oh, Gigi, I see you're here

17:34.487 --> 17:36.354
having a good time
with your best friend,

17:36.356 --> 17:39.590
while I'm over here having
an equally good time with mine.

17:39.592 --> 17:40.725
Dre, why you being weird?

17:40.727 --> 17:42.026
I'm not being weird.
Yes, you are.

17:42.028 --> 17:43.694
<i>You're</i> the one
being weird, weirdo.

17:43.696 --> 17:45.029
<i>You</i> abandoned the friendship.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.931
Oh, hey, Ellen. Gigi.

17:46.933 --> 17:48.199
[ Speaking Vietnamese ]
Viet Cong. [ Chuckles ]

17:48.201 --> 17:49.667
Viet Cong?
Yeah.

17:49.669 --> 17:51.035
Who you calling viet Cong? You.

17:51.037 --> 17:52.437
You, viet Cong, fool! What
are you gonna do about it?!

17:52.439 --> 17:53.905
What are you gonna do?
"Fool"?!

17:53.907 --> 17:55.106
I'm tired of you acting like
you're 2 years old up in here!

17:55.108 --> 17:56.374
Wait, whatever.
You're causing a scene.

17:56.376 --> 17:58.042
W-what are you talking about?
I was your plus-one.

17:58.044 --> 17:59.544
[ Both shouting indistinctly ]
Okay, well, you must be Napoleon.

17:59.546 --> 18:01.412
Help me, please.
Hi, I'm... what?

18:01.414 --> 18:02.914
Gigi's crazy!

18:02.916 --> 18:05.750
I'm a grown man
in hot-wax mittens.

18:05.752 --> 18:07.518
[ Sighs ] She Dutch-ovened
me in my Tesla!

18:07.520 --> 18:08.753
Now the battery's not working!

18:08.755 --> 18:10.054
Wait a minute.
What are you saying?

18:10.056 --> 18:11.789
I-I don't have to
deal with this.

18:11.791 --> 18:14.258
I produced the vmas.
I have choices.

18:14.260 --> 18:16.861
Well, I have choices, too.
I am a doctor.

18:16.863 --> 18:19.297
These hands were
in brain surgery yesterday.

18:19.299 --> 18:21.732
These hands told Wiz Khalifa
to wrap it up.

18:21.734 --> 18:22.967
You did this!

18:22.969 --> 18:24.635
You're the one that said
their friendship was weird!

18:24.637 --> 18:26.637
It<i> is</i> weird.
Look at them.

18:26.639 --> 18:28.439
[ Conversing in Vietnamese ]

18:28.441 --> 18:29.807
Oh!

18:29.809 --> 18:31.242
Dre: Didn't think I was gonna
come back with that one, did you?

18:31.244 --> 18:33.077
Well, at least they're
weird together. Yeah.

18:33.079 --> 18:35.913
I say we get out of here...
While we can.

18:35.915 --> 18:37.615
Good idea.
I'm going.

18:37.617 --> 18:39.750
She's gonna pay.

18:39.752 --> 18:41.119
Dre:
Are you kidding me?

18:41.121 --> 18:42.887
Did they just walk out of here
without saying goodbye?

18:42.889 --> 18:44.288
That's totally rude.

18:44.290 --> 18:45.823
At least he is.

18:45.825 --> 18:47.925
Hey, I-i thought
you and him were cool.

18:47.927 --> 18:50.428
Oh, no, we're cool. I mean,
he might be the one. Oh.

18:50.430 --> 18:52.430
But he is so boring
to go shopping with.

18:52.432 --> 18:55.266
His body is all, like,
"boom, boom, boom."

18:55.268 --> 18:57.435
It's, like, perfect.
There's no challenge.

18:57.437 --> 18:59.103
But you, on the other hand...

18:59.105 --> 19:02.340
I'll take your weird "little man
Tate" body to Fred segal any day.

19:02.342 --> 19:04.275
Oh, that's so sweet.

19:04.277 --> 19:05.443
[ Both laugh ]

19:05.445 --> 19:06.811
Well, since
we're being honest...

19:06.813 --> 19:07.845
What?

19:07.847 --> 19:09.447
Shopping with bow is
no challenge, either.

19:09.449 --> 19:10.648
Really, why?

19:10.650 --> 19:12.350
Yeah, she ain't got
the same problems you got...

19:12.352 --> 19:14.252
Hats, visors, headbands.

19:14.254 --> 19:15.486
She can just buy off the rack.

19:15.488 --> 19:16.754
I mean, she ain't got
to let nothing out.

19:16.756 --> 19:17.922
Ah.

19:17.924 --> 19:19.457
Yeah, it don't stretch it
when she put it on.

19:19.459 --> 19:20.825
Uh-huh.
Mm-hmm.

19:20.827 --> 19:22.960
I miss you.
I miss you, too.

19:22.962 --> 19:24.996
And I'm so sorry
I bailed on you.

19:24.998 --> 19:27.598
But I like Napoleon so much.

19:27.600 --> 19:30.034
Hmm.
And I want babies.

19:30.036 --> 19:32.503
And I want my babies
to play with your babies

19:32.505 --> 19:34.772
and then grow up and be
best friends like me and you.

19:34.774 --> 19:38.442
Hey, we're never going to stop
growing up together.

19:38.444 --> 19:40.945
You're my sis, and I love you.

19:40.947 --> 19:42.113
Oh, I love you, too.

19:42.115 --> 19:45.650
Come on, girl. Give me some.
[ Chuckles ]

19:45.652 --> 19:47.485
I'm sorry I started tripping.

19:47.487 --> 19:49.287
It's okay.
All right.

19:49.289 --> 19:51.122
[ Children laughing ]

19:51.124 --> 19:53.124
Hey, bow.
Mm-hmm?

19:53.126 --> 19:55.359
I need to talk to you
about something. Yeah?

19:55.361 --> 19:57.862
Gigi and I...
We need to be best friends.

19:57.864 --> 19:59.363
Good.

19:59.365 --> 20:01.899
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
You don't understand.

20:01.901 --> 20:03.701
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.
I do. I do.

20:03.703 --> 20:07.405
I do<i> not</i> want to be
your best friend.

20:07.407 --> 20:08.706
Oh, thank god.
Right?

20:08.708 --> 20:11.008
I mean, I was bothered
by what you have with Gigi,

20:11.010 --> 20:15.313
and then I realized
it is a ridiculous waste of time

20:15.315 --> 20:19.317
with no merit or meaning
or lasting benefit on society.

20:19.319 --> 20:22.887
It's like a... like a drain
of global spiritual energy.

20:22.889 --> 20:24.488
It's like [Imitates suction]
okay, you know, I-i-i feel like

20:24.490 --> 20:25.590
you're trying
to get to something else.

20:25.592 --> 20:27.225
What's...
Oh.

20:27.227 --> 20:28.593
Oh, you're right.
You're right. Okay.

20:28.595 --> 20:29.827
[ Inhales deeply ]

20:29.829 --> 20:33.164
I am not jealous of what you
have with anybody else

20:33.166 --> 20:35.566
because I love
what I have with you.

20:35.568 --> 20:36.834
Works for me.

20:36.836 --> 20:38.936
[ "It had to be you" plays ]
Muah. I love you.

20:38.938 --> 20:40.371
Ohh, I love you, baby.

20:40.373 --> 20:41.606
We love each other.
A lot.

20:41.608 --> 20:42.907
[ Both chuckle ]

20:42.909 --> 20:44.869
Together: But we are<i> not</i>
each other's best friend.

20:47.914 --> 20:49.714
♪ I keep on fallin' ♪

20:49.716 --> 20:53.551
♪ Iiiiiin love ♪

20:53.553 --> 20:54.585
♪ Go, didi ♪

20:54.587 --> 20:56.420
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

20:56.422 --> 20:58.756
♪ In and out of love ♪

20:58.758 --> 21:02.059
♪ With you ♪

